{
  "stem": "13469.7",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was quite difficult to explain to these Russian soldiers and some officers who we were.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, we'd been in the camps with our shaven heads or that we were Jews, that we were persecuted and all this sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So eventually we managed to convince them that we were on their side, kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, and they said, you know-- let us go.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and we all put-- instead of the yellow stars, we all put big badges on-- red, white, and blue-- to show that we were from Holland, kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, and that was sort of the password as far as the Russians were concerned.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they let us go, carry on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They took no notice of us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They carried on.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because that was on the 23rd of April, 1945.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We'd been on the train for exactly two weeks, and we'd been liberated.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Two days later, the Russian army, on the 25th of April, met the American army at Torgau just down the road from where we were.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And, and there are lots of pictures in the papers about that-- the Russians meeting the Americans at the River Elbe, at Torgau.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that was two days after we were liberated, very close to where we were.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But we went about our business in the normal way as we'd been used to on the, on the train.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And in the evening, the first evening of liberation, I came back to the train with my raw potatoes and my greens, you see.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And, and, and [NON-ENGLISH] and, and most of the other people, they had been to the nearby village of Trebitz, and they came back with white bread and honey and milk.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
